'248'=>'
<h1>'.trans('doctrine-3.Erroneous views (THESE ARE FALSE VIEWS!)').'</h1>
<h2>'.trans('doctrine-3.Sabellianism').'</h2>
<h3>'.trans('doctrine-3.Bishop Sabellius taught that Father&#44; Son&#44; and Holy Ghost are simply three aspects or manifestations of God.').'</h3>
<h3>'.trans('doctrine-3.There are three manifestations of one God.').'</h3>
<h4>'.trans('doctrine-3.Sometimes this is referred to as three personalities.').'</h4>
<h4>'.trans('doctrine-3.God does not have split personalities.').'</h4>
<h3>'.trans('doctrine-3.Oneness teaching falls under this category.').'</h3>
<h3>'.trans('doctrine-3.Refutation to this view').'</h3>
<h4>'.trans('doctrine-3.Scripture clearly teaches the plurality of the Godhea').'</h4>
<p>'.trans('doctrine-3.Elohim is a plural noun.').'</p>
<blockquote>'.trans('doctrine-3.In the beginning God created the heaven and the earth. (Gen 1:1)').'</blockquote>
<p>'.trans('doctrine-3.Plural pronouns used to refer to God.').'</p>
<blockquote>'.trans('doctrine-3.And God said&#44; Let us make man in our image&#44; after our likenessâ€¦ (Gen. 1:18)').'</blockquote>
<p>'.trans('doctrine-3.The Bible reveals there are three persons within One God.').'</p>
<blockquote>'.trans('doctrine-3.1 John 5:7 -- For there are three that bear record in heaven&#44; the Father&#44; the Word&#44; and the Holy Ghost: and these three are one.').'</blockquote> 
<h4>'.trans('doctrine-3.There are sharp distinctions revealed in Scripture between The Father&#44; Son&#44; and Holy Spirit.').'</h4>
<p>'.trans('doctrine-3.The Father sent The Son').' &mdash;</p>
<blockquote>'.trans('doctrine-3.For God so loved the world&#44; that he gave his only begotten Son&#44; that whosoever believeth in him should not perish&#44; but have everlasting life (John 3:16) I came forth from the Father&#44; and am come into the world: again&#44; I leave the world&#44; and go to the Father. (Joh 16:28)').'</blockquote>
<p>'.trans('doctrine-3.The Son returns to The Father --').'</p>
<blockquote>'.trans('doctrine-3.Jesus saith unto her&#44; Touch me not; for I am not yet ascended to my Father: but go to my brethren&#44; and say unto them&#44; I ascend unto my Father&#44; and your Father; and to my God&#44; and your God. (Joh 20:17) A little while&#44; and ye shall not see me: and again&#44; a little while&#44; and ye shall see me&#44; because I go to the Father. (Joh 16:16)').'</blockquote>
<p>'.trans('doctrine-3.The Father and Son send The Spirit --').'</p>
<blockquote>'.trans('doctrine-3.But when the Comforter is come&#44; whom I will send unto you from the Father&#44; even the Spirit of truth&#44; which proceedeth from the Father&#44; he shall testify of me:(Joh 15:26)Nevertheless I tell you the truth; It is expedient for you that I go away: for if I go not away&#44; the Comforter will not come unto you; but if I depart&#44; I will send him unto you. (Joh 16:7)').'</blockquote>
<p>'.trans('doctrine-3.The Spirit intercedes with The Father.').'</p>
<blockquote>'.trans('doctrine-3.Likewise the Spirit also helpeth our infirmities: for we know not what we should pray for as we ought: but the Spirit itself maketh intercession for us with groanings which cannot be uttered. (Rom 8:26)').'</blockquote>
<h4>'.trans('doctrine-3.The Bible defines the oneness of God.').'</h4>
<blockquote>'.trans('doctrine-3.And the glory which thou gavest me I have given them; that they may be one&#44; even as we are one: (Joh 17:26).').'</blockquote>
<p>'.trans('doctrine-3.The body is one in unity&#44; yet many in person.').'</p>
<blockquote>'.trans('doctrine-3.Wherefore they are no more twain&#44; but one flesh. What therefore God hath joined together&#44; let not man put asunder. (Mat 19:6)').'</blockquote>
<p>'.trans('doctrine-3.Husband and wife become one&#44; yet there are still two persons.').'</p>
<h2>'.trans('doctrine-3.Arianism').'</h2>
<h3>'.trans('doctrine-3.Arius').'</h3>
<h4>'.trans('doctrine-3.Presbyter of Alexandria about 318 AD').'</h4>
<h4>'.trans('doctrine-3.Taught the Son is subordinate to the Father').'</h4>
